These JSON files are snapshots of TargetConfig extracted from Hubris
archives at a point in time.  They are used as test data for the
assembler's unit and fixture tests, allowing tests to run without
access to a Hubris archive or build environment.

These fixtures WILL go stale as Hubris evolves (Idol interfaces
change, devices are added, features are renamed).  They should not
be used as a source of truth for what a live target supports.

To regenerate from a current archive:

    HUBRIS_ARCHIVE=path/to/archive.zip GENERATE_FIXTURE=1 \
        cargo test -p humility-hif-assembler \
            --test archive_integration generate_fixture \
            -- --nocapture
